         Ok, I had to interfere here...</P><P>- First ToN, 720 dmg for 405 mana is a VERY good spell.... you heal <BR>AND nuke.<BR>How many times clerics where surprised (sebilis, katta) when I tell <BR>them, plz no heal, and then they see my HP bar gain at least 2 red <BR>bubbles.</P><P>How many times it happened to me to pull with only 1 red and half <BR>bubble cause I know I am gonna gain it back !<BR>And yes I know , no need to quote this, but thats why I die maybe too <BR>much for a necro :-)</P><P>- Second : with AA Xp or focus items... thats much more (with mage <BR>focus item, I ToN for 863)</P><P>- Third : If soloing I never use ToN, Vexing is much more mana <BR>efficient, and a deflux for emergencies.</P><P>- Four : The point with KEI is not that this spell makes chanter too <BR>close from us necro...<BR>remember they can mana tap a mob for very cheap.</P><P>The REAL point with KEI, is that all classes have ther mana regen <BR>rate, somtimes new ones (Improved familiar for Wizards).. but for<BR>ALL these classes, KEI stacks , so every class gets , with time, <BR>better and better mana regen. Of course that means they need a <BR>chanter with them.</P><P>So thats why we can ask for : KEI should stack with Lich !</P><P>If we group with a chanter we can benefit from KEI like every one.<BR>No reason to not have it stack.</P><P>Even in spectral form a chanter can clear my mind ;-)</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73541" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73541</a><BR>Megabita<BR>Warlock From Divine Legend<BR>On Terris-Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
